    <item>
      <title>Domestic Horticulturalists</title>
      <link>https://apophenian.art/poetry/domestic-horticulturalists/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://apophenian.art/poetry/domestic-horticulturalists/</guid>
      <description>The grass has grown so long,
It is underfoot no more.
It is around our ankles,
Our knees,
Our eyes.
A green jungle,
The blue sky.
A tiger like kitten
Prowls the grasslands and prairies of our love.
A rumbling purr,
A quiet resentment,
A long past feeling of order and restraint.
A painful clarity and of course,
The hopeless boredom
Of you
And me
And our contempt for gardening.</description>
